   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>MH 4328, recto: (1) The humblest John writes greeting (2) his beloved brother.  Seeing that I sent (3) to you some days ago, saying: 'Come north to me (4) on this business,' and you came before the men had reached an agreement, (5) and you went away, now take two (6) solidi and come north to me quickly, (7) they being full weight on the standard of this district, for there is (8) need.  (9) Farewell in the Lord at all times.</ab>
         </div>
